{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781763740949,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"id":"prt_ed9651514001fVsb8stx1iHxc2","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","snapshot":"6fc0e696419bc396c4e74f759feff0373c542308","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1781763751089,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"id":"prt_ed96525670017N1EWJZzzZDKyR","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","type":"text","text":"The loop will run as a single-iteration lineage: initialize state, perform one evidence-backed review pass, then synthesize with `maxIterationsReached`. Next I’m checking the target scope and current implementation files to anchor findings.","time":{"start":1781763745127,"end":1781763751084},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea116e48191bb7d97ac3148f646","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763751142,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JUh9LsvPZNsx6W03u2YzJwSS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n14: \n15: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n26: \n27: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n28: |---------|--------|------|\n29: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n30: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n31: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n32: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n33: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n34: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n35: \n36: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n41: \n42: The registry groups findings into:\n43: \n44: - Active findings.\n45: - Resolved findings.\n46: - Repeated findings.\n47: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n48: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n49: \n50: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n55: \n56: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n57: \n58: Recovery order:\n59: \n60: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n61: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n62: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n63: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n68: \n69: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n70: \n71: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n72: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n73: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n74: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n75: \n76: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n81: \n82: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n83: \n84: ### Two-Tier Match\n85: \n86: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n87:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n88:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n89:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n90:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n91: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n92: \n93: ### Synthesis Behavior\n94: \n95: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n96: \n97: ### Emission Requirement\n98: \n99: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n104: \n105: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n106: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n107: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n108: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":108,"totalLines":108,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781763751123,"end":1781763751139}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea706f481918400f12a6ca81755"}},"id":"prt_ed9653caf001kb8trgZxXzt8GO","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763751142,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d1O6J4mKMI58qg5Lq9dvGHz9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n14: \n15: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n22: \n23: ### Usage\n24: \n25: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n26: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n27: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n28: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n29: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. TOPIC\n34: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n40: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n41: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n42: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n43: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n44: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n49: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n54: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n59: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n60: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n61: \n62: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n63: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n64: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n65: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n70: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n71: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n72: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n73: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n74: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n75: \n76: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n77: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n82: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n83: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n88: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n89: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n94: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n95: \n96: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n97: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n98: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n99: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n100: \n101: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n102: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n103: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n108: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n109: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n114: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n115: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n121: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n126: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n127: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n128: \n129: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n130: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n131: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n132: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n133: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n134: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n135: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n136: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n137: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n142: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n143: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n144: \n145: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n146: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n147: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n148: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n153: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n154: - Max iterations: [from config]\n155: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n156: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n157: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n158: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n159: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n160: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n161: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n162: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n163: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n164: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n165: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n166: - Started: [timestamp]\n167: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n172: \n173: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n174: \n175: ```markdown\n176: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n177: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n178: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n179: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n180: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n181: \n182: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n183: - Dimension: test-coverage\n184: - Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n185: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n186: \n187: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n188: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n189: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n190: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n191: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n192: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n193: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n194: ```\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781763751129,"end":1781763751141}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea7070881919639744e600695c3"}},"id":"prt_ed9653cd7001VjSoJXPcX7xrH5","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763751144,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_667P2yBwUL3ZbDNUwyov6rGA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review dashboard\"\n6:   - \"review session overview\"\n7:   - \"review findings summary\"\n8:   - \"review coverage trend\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: general\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n14: \n15: Auto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n22: 1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n23: 2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n24: 3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n29: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n30: - **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n31: - **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. STATUS\n36: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n37: - Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n38: - Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n39: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n40: - Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n41: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n42: - Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n43: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n44: - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n45: - hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n51: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n52: - **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n53: - **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n54: - **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n55: - **Repeated findings:** [N]\n56: - **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n57: - **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n58: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. PROGRESS\n63: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n64: \n65: | # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n66: |---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n67: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n68: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 5. COVERAGE\n73: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n74: - Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n75: - Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n76: - Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n77: - Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 6. TREND\n83: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n84: - Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n85: - New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n86: - Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n87: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n92: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n93: - **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n94: - **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n95: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n100: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n101: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n102: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n107: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n108: - [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n114: \n115: Reference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n116: \n117: ```markdown\n118: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n119: \n120: ## 2. STATUS\n121: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n122: - Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n123: - Status: ITERATING\n124: - Iteration: 4 of 7\n125: - Verdict: PENDING\n126: - Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n127: \n128: ## 3. PROGRESS\n129: \n130: | # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n131: |---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n132: | 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n133: | 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n134: | 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n135: | 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n136: \n137: ## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n138: - Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n139: - Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n140: - Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n141: \n142: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n143: - 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n144: - agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n145: ```\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n- Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n- hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **Repeated findings:** [N]\n- **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n- **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. PROGRESS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n| # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n- Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n- Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 6. TREND\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n- New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n- **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n- Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 4 of 7\n- Verdict: PENDING\n- Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n|---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n| 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n| 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n| 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n| 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n\n## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n- Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n- Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n- Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n- 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n- agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781763751136,"end":1781763751143}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea707108191a8263537b941307e"}},"id":"prt_ed9653cda001jZ7Yw0W8QCdSk8","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763751158,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4h337bi9mP7SlOjhjrV4uWDp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n2: # This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n3: # convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n4: # and validation expectations.\n5: \n6: meta:\n7:   ownerSkill: deep-review\n8:   reviewModeVersion: 2\n9:   generatedNotice:\n10:     warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n11:     beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n12:     endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n13:   sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n14: \n15: # Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\n16: contract:\n17:   defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n18: \n19:   # Review target taxonomy.\n20:   targetTypes:\n21:     - id: spec-folder\n22:       cliValue: spec-folder\n23:       label: Spec Folder\n24:       description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n25:     - id: skill\n26:       cliValue: skill\n27:       label: Skill\n28:       description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n29:     - id: agent\n30:       cliValue: agent\n31:       label: Agent\n32:       description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n33:     - id: track\n34:       cliValue: track\n35:       label: Track\n36:       description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n37:     - id: files\n38:       cliValue: files\n39:       label: Files\n40:       description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n41: \n42:   # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n43:   # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n44:   dimensions:\n45:     - id: correctness\n46:       priority: 1\n47:       label: Correctness\n48:       checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n49:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n50:     - id: security\n51:       priority: 2\n52:       label: Security\n53:       checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n54:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n55:     - id: traceability\n56:       priority: 3\n57:       label: Traceability\n58:       checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n59:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n60:     - id: maintainability\n61:       priority: 4\n62:       label: Maintainability\n63:       checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n64:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n65: \n66:   # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n67:   severities:\n68:     - id: P0\n69:       weight: 10.0\n70:       label: Blocker\n71:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n72:     - id: P1\n73:       weight: 5.0\n74:       label: Required\n75:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n76:     - id: P2\n77:       weight: 1.0\n78:       label: Suggestion\n79:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n80: \n81:   # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n82:   verdicts:\n83:     - id: FAIL\n84:       label: Fail\n85:       condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n86:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n87:     - id: CONDITIONAL\n88:       label: Conditional\n89:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n90:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n91:     - id: PASS\n92:       label: Pass\n93:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n94:       hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n95:       nextCommand: /create:changelog\n96: \n97:   # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n98:   qualityGates:\n99:     - id: evidence\n100:       label: Evidence\n101:       binary: true\n102:       combines:\n103:         - evidence-completeness\n104:         - no-inference-only\n105:       rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n106:     - id: scope\n107:       label: Scope\n108:       binary: true\n109:       combines:\n110:         - scope-alignment\n111:       rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n112:     - id: coverage\n113:       label: Coverage\n114:       binary: true\n115:       combines:\n116:         - severity-coverage\n117:         - cross-reference\n118:       rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n119: \n120:   # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n121:   convergence:\n122:     defaults:\n123:       maxIterations: 7\n124:       convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n125:       stuckThreshold: 2\n126:     signals:\n127:       - id: rolling-average\n128:         weight: 0.30\n129:         description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n130:       - id: mad-noise-floor\n131:         weight: 0.25\n132:         description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n133:       - id: dimension-coverage\n134:         weight: 0.45\n135:         description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n136:     severityMath:\n137:       refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n138:       p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n139:       noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n140:     coverageAge:\n141:       minStabilizationPasses: 1\n142:     thresholds:\n143:       rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n144:       noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n145:       compositeStopScore: 0.60\n146: \n147:   lifecycleModes:\n148:     - id: new\n149:       description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n150:     - id: resume\n151:       description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n152:     - id: restart\n153:       description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n154:     - id: fork\n155:       status: deferred\n156:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n157:     - id: completed-continue\n158:       status: deferred\n159:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n160: \n161:   lineageFields:\n162:     - sessionId\n163:     - parentSessionId\n164:     - lineageMode\n165:     - generation\n166:     - continuedFromRun\n167: \n168:   reducer:\n169:     enabled: true\n170:     inputs:\n171:       - latestJSONLDelta\n172:       - newIterationFile\n173:       - priorReducedState\n174:     outputs:\n175:       - findingsRegistry\n176:       - dashboardMetrics\n177:       - strategyUpdates\n178:     failureModes:\n179:       malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n180:       missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n181:       schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n182:     idempotent: true\n183: \n184:   releaseReadinessStates:\n185:     - id: in-progress\n186:       description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n187:     - id: converged\n188:       description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n189:     - id: release-blocking\n190:       description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n191: \n192:   # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n193:   # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n194:   crossReferenceProtocols:\n195:     - id: spec_code\n196:       dimension: traceability\n197:       level: core\n198:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n199:       gateClass: hard\n200:       passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n201:       partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n202:       failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n203:     - id: checklist_evidence\n204:       dimension: traceability\n205:       level: core\n206:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n207:       gateClass: hard\n208:       passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n209:       partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n210:       failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n211:     - id: skill_agent\n212:       dimension: traceability\n213:       level: overlay\n214:       appliesTo: [skill]\n215:       gateClass: advisory\n216:       passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n217:       partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n218:       failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n219:     - id: agent_cross_runtime\n220:       dimension: traceability\n221:       level: overlay\n222:       appliesTo: [agent]\n223:       gateClass: advisory\n224:       passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n225:       partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n226:       failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n227:     - id: feature_catalog_code\n228:       dimension: traceability\n229:       level: overlay\n230:       appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n231:       gateClass: advisory\n232:       passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n233:       partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n234:       failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n235:     - id: playbook_capability\n236:       dimension: traceability\n237:       level: overlay\n238:       appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n239:       gateClass: advisory\n240:       passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n241:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n242:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n243: \n244:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n245:   outputs:\n246:     config:\n247:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n248:       machineOwned: false\n249:       fields:\n250:         - sessionId\n251:         - parentSessionId\n252:         - lineageMode\n253:         - generation\n254:         - continuedFromRun\n255:         - releaseReadinessState\n256:     findingsRegistry:\n257:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n258:       machineOwned: true\n259:       sections:\n260:         - openFindings\n261:         - resolvedFindings\n262:         - repeatedFindings\n263:         - dimensionCoverage\n264:         - findingsBySeverity\n265:         - convergenceScore\n266:     reviewReport:\n267:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n268:       sections:\n269:         - executive-summary\n270:         - planning-trigger\n271:         - active-finding-registry\n272:         - remediation-workstreams\n273:         - spec-seed\n274:         - plan-seed\n275:         - traceability-status\n276:         - deferred-items\n277:         - audit-appendix\n278:     strategy:\n279:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n280:       requiredSections:\n281:         - topic\n282:         - review-dimensions\n283:         - completed-dimensions\n284:         - running-findings\n285:         - what-worked\n286:         - what-failed\n287:         - exhausted-approaches\n288:         - ruled-out-directions\n289:         - next-focus\n290:         - known-context\n291:         - cross-reference-status\n292:         - files-under-review\n293:         - review-boundaries\n294:     dashboard:\n295:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n296:       machineOwned: true\n297:       sections:\n298:         - status\n299:         - findings-summary\n300:         - dimension-coverage\n301:         - progress\n302:         - next-focus\n303:     pauseSentinel:\n304:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n305:       machineOwned: false\n306:       description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n307:     jsonl:\n308:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n309:       iterationRecord:\n310:         required:\n311:           - type\n312:           - mode\n313:           - run\n314:           - status\n315:           - focus\n316:           - dimensions\n317:           - filesReviewed\n318:           - findingsCount\n319:           - findingsSummary\n320:           - findingsNew\n321:           - findingDetails\n322:           - newFindingsRatio\n323:           - sessionId\n324:           - generation\n325:           - lineageMode\n326:           - timestamp\n327:           - durationMs\n328:         optional:\n329:           - parentSessionId\n330:           - continuedFromRun\n331:           - findingsRefined\n332:           - findingRefs\n333:           - traceabilityChecks\n334:           - coverage\n335:           - noveltyJustification\n336:           - ruledOut\n337:           - focusTrack\n338:           - scoreEstimate\n339:           - segment\n340:           - convergenceSignals\n341:           - graphEvents\n342:       synthesisEvent:\n343:         required:\n344:           - type\n345:           - event\n346:           - mode\n347:           - totalIterations\n348:           - verdict\n349:           - activeP0\n350:           - activeP1\n351:           - activeP2\n352:           - dimensionCoverage\n353:           - stopReason\n354:           - timestamp\n355: \n356: # Render targets define where generated or mixed-authored contract fragments land.\n357: render:\n358:   artifacts:\n359:     - id: workflow-auto\n360:       path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n361:       ownership: mixed\n362:       format: yaml\n363:       markers:\n364:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n365:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n366:       sections:\n367:         - target-types\n368:         - dimensions\n369:         - verdicts\n370:         - quality-gates\n371:         - convergence\n372:         - cross-reference-protocols\n373:     - id: workflow-confirm\n374:       path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n375:       ownership: mixed\n376:       format: yaml\n377:       markers:\n378:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n379:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n380:       sections:\n381:         - target-types\n382:         - dimensions\n383:         - verdicts\n384:         - quality-gates\n385:         - convergence\n386:         - cross-reference-protocols\n387:     - id: agent-opencode\n388:       path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n389:       ownership: mixed\n390:       format: markdown\n391:       markers:\n392:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n393:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n394:       sections:\n395:         - dimensions\n396:         - severities\n397:         - quality-gates\n398:         - cross-reference-protocols\n399:         - outputs\n400:     - id: agent-claude\n401:       path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n402:       ownership: mixed\n403:       format: markdown\n404:       markers:\n405:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n406:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n407:       sections:\n408:         - dimensions\n409:         - severities\n410:         - quality-gates\n411:         - cross-reference-protocols\n412:         - outputs\n413:     - id: agent-codex\n414:       path: .codex/agents/deep-review.toml\n415:       ownership: mixed\n416:       format: toml\n417:       markers:\n418:         begin: \"# BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n419:         end: \"# END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n420:       sections:\n421:         - dimensions\n422:         - severities\n423:         - quality-gates\n424:         - cross-reference-protocols\n425:         - outputs\n426:     - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n427:       path: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n428:       ownership: mixed\n429:       format: markdown\n430:       markers:\n431:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n432:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n433:       sections:\n434:         - target-types\n435:         - dimensions\n436:         - verdicts\n437:         - quality-gates\n438:         - outputs\n439:     - id: review-contract-snapshot\n440:       path: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n441:       ownership: generated\n442:       format: markdown\n443:       markers:\n444:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n445:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n446:       sections:\n447:         - meta\n448:         - target-types\n449:         - dimensions\n450:         - severities\n451:         - verdicts\n452:         - quality-gates\n453:         - convergence\n454:         - cross-reference-protocols\n455:         - outputs\n456:         - validation\n457: \n458: # Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\n459: validation:\n460:   schemaVersion: 1\n461:   checks:\n462:     - id: schema\n463:       description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n464:     - id: render-verify\n465:       description: Re-render downstream artifacts in verify mode and fail on drift.\n466:     - id: marker-integrity\n467:       description: Ensure every render target contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n468:     - id: enum-parity\n469:       description: Ensure target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, and quality gates match across rendered artifacts.\n470:     - id: jsonl-parity\n471:       description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n472:     - id: lifecycle-parity\n473:       description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n474:     - id: reducer-contract\n475:       description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n476:     - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n477:       description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n478:     - id: runtime-coverage\n479:       description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared render artifact and parity coverage.\n480:     - id: playbook-assertions\n481:       description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.\n\n(End of file - total 481 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n    beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n    endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","text":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Generated from review_mode_contract.yaml. Do not manually edit generated sections.\"\n    beginMarker: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n    endMarker: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract -->\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:\n    - id: spec-folder\n      cliValue: spec-folder\n      label: Spec Folder\n      description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n    - id: skill\n      cliValue: skill\n      label: Skill\n      description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n    - id: agent\n      cliValue: agent\n      label: Agent\n      description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n    - id: track\n      cliValue: track\n      label: Track\n      description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n    - id: files\n      cliValue: files\n      label: Files\n      description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n\n  # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n  # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n  dimensions:\n    - id: correctness\n      priority: 1\n      label: Correctness\n      checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: security\n      priority: 2\n      label: Security\n      checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: traceability\n      priority: 3\n      label: Traceability\n      checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n    - id: maintainability\n      priority: 4\n      label: Maintainability\n      checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n\n  # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n  severities:\n    - id: P0\n      weight: 10.0\n      label: Blocker\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P1\n      weight: 5.0\n      label: Required\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P2\n      weight: 1.0\n      label: Suggestion\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n\n  # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n  verdicts:\n    - id: FAIL\n      label: Fail\n      condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: CONDITIONAL\n      label: Conditional\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: PASS\n      label: Pass\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n      hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n      nextCommand: /create:changelog\n\n  # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n  qualityGates:\n    - id: evidence\n      label: Evidence\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - evidence-completeness\n        - no-inference-only\n      rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n    - id: scope\n      label: Scope\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - scope-alignment\n      rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n    - id: coverage\n      label: Coverage\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - severity-coverage\n        - cross-reference\n      rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n\n  # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n  convergence:\n    defaults:\n      maxIterations: 7\n      convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n      stuckThreshold: 2\n    signals:\n      - id: rolling-average\n        weight: 0.30\n        description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n      - id: mad-noise-floor\n        weight: 0.25\n        description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n      - id: dimension-coverage\n        weight: 0.45\n        description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n    severityMath:\n      refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n      p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n      noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n    coverageAge:\n      minStabilizationPasses: 1\n    thresholds:\n      rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n      noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n      compositeStopScore: 0.60\n\n  lifecycleModes:\n    - id: new\n      description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n    - id: resume\n      description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n    - id: restart\n      description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n    - id: fork\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n    - id: completed-continue\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n\n  lineageFields:\n    - sessionId\n    - parentSessionId\n    - lineageMode\n    - generation\n    - continuedFromRun\n\n  reducer:\n    enabled: true\n    inputs:\n      - latestJSONLDelta\n      - newIterationFile\n      - priorReducedState\n    outputs:\n      - findingsRegistry\n      - dashboardMetrics\n      - strategyUpdates\n    failureModes:\n      malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n      missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n      schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n    idempotent: true\n\n  releaseReadinessStates:\n    - id: in-progress\n      description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n    - id: converged\n      description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n    - id: release-blocking\n      description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n\n  # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n  # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n  crossReferenceProtocols:\n    - id: spec_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n      partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n      failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n    - id: checklist_evidence\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n      partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n      failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n    - id: skill_agent\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n      partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n      failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n    - id: agent_cross_runtime\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [agent]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n      partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n      failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n    - id: feature_catalog_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n      partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n      failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n    - id: playbook_capability\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings\n        - resolvedFindings\n        - repeatedFindings\n        - dimensionCoverage\n        - findingsBySeverity\n        - convergenceScore\n    reviewReport:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n      sections:\n        - executive-summary\n        - planning-trigger\n        - active-finding-registry\n        - remediation-workstreams\n        - spec-seed\n        - plan-seed\n        - traceability-status\n        - deferred-items\n        - audit-appendix\n    strategy:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n      requiredSections:\n        - topic\n        - review-dimensions\n        - completed-dimensions\n        - running-findings\n        - what-worked\n        - what-failed\n        - exhausted-approaches\n        - ruled-out-directions\n        - next-focus\n        - known-context\n        - cross-reference-status\n        - files-under-review\n        - review-boundaries\n    dashboard:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - status\n        - findings-summary\n        - dimension-coverage\n        - progress\n        - next-focus\n    pauseSentinel:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n    jsonl:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n      iterationRecord:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - mode\n          - run\n          - status\n          - focus\n          - dimensions\n          - filesReviewed\n          - findingsCount\n          - findingsSummary\n          - findingsNew\n          - findingDetails\n          - newFindingsRatio\n          - sessionId\n          - generation\n          - lineageMode\n          - timestamp\n          - durationMs\n        optional:\n          - parentSessionId\n          - continuedFromRun\n          - findingsRefined\n          - findingRefs\n          - traceabilityChecks\n          - coverage\n          - noveltyJustification\n          - ruledOut\n          - focusTrack\n          - scoreEstimate\n          - segment\n          - convergenceSignals\n          - graphEvents\n      synthesisEvent:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - event\n          - mode\n          - totalIterations\n          - verdict\n          - activeP0\n          - activeP1\n          - activeP2\n          - dimensionCoverage\n          - stopReason\n          - timestamp\n\n# Render targets define where generated or mixed-authored contract fragments land.\nrender:\n  artifacts:\n    - id: workflow-auto\n      path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: yaml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n    - id: workflow-confirm\n      path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: yaml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n    - id: agent-opencode\n      path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: agent-claude\n      path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: agent-codex\n      path: .codex/agents/deep-review.toml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: toml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"# BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n        end: \"# END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n      path: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - outputs\n    - id: review-contract-snapshot\n      path: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n      ownership: generated\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n      sections:\n        - meta\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n        - validation\n\n# Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\nvalidation:\n  schemaVersion: 1\n  checks:\n    - id: schema\n      description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n    - id: render-verify\n      description: Re-render downstream artifacts in verify mode and fail on drift.\n    - id: marker-integrity\n      description: Ensure every render target contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n    - id: enum-parity\n      description: Ensure target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, and quality gates match across rendered artifacts.\n    - id: jsonl-parity\n      description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n    - id: lifecycle-parity\n      description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n    - id: reducer-contract\n      description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n    - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n      description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n    - id: runtime-coverage\n      description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared render artifact and parity coverage.\n    - id: playbook-assertions\n      description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":481,"totalLines":481,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","time":{"start":1781763751149,"end":1781763751157}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea707188191a1f8c5b545a56082"}},"id":"prt_ed9653ce0001n1sddvWe57jotL","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781763751160,"sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6FmpzagXuM75bJzGDcgdgIAm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: All paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n8: - `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n9: - `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n10: - `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n11: - BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n12: - the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n13: \n14: ## Review dimensions\n15: correctness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n16: \n17: ## Notes\n18: Round-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.\n19: \n20: ## If MCP tools hang or error\n21: The `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back — use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit — direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n- `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n- `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n- BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n- the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n\n## Notes\nRound-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n- `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n- `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n- BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n- the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n\n## Notes\nRound-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error\nThe `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back — use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit — direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":21,"totalLines":21,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","time":{"start":1781763751151,"end":1781763751159}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e883ac7af2860b0016a338ea707208191972951403924b24c"}},"id":"prt_ed9653cee001OFRlldxQUfFRXj","sessionID":"ses_1269bed27ffeaBceEWnTAdPS3b","messageID":"msg_ed9650e7b0019H7VWJYMyWXr7S"}}
